text: The year 2102 is 75 years after the current year (2025). It is a common year, meaning it is not a leap year. The Jewish New Year (Rosh Hashanah) in 2102 begins on September 13 and ends on September 15. In the Gregorian calendar, year 2102 is a common year and not a leap year. It will have 365 days. Specifically, year 2102 will follow the common year rule of not being divisible by 400 if it is a multiple of 100.
